Quick Ratio = (Cash on Hand + Bank Deposits + Interest Receivable + Accounts Receivable) / Total Current Liabilities

Step 1: Sum of quick assets (exclude Inventory)
- Cash on Hand = 4,560,423.24
- Bank Deposits = 3,655,000.00
- Interest Receivable = 10,051.66
- Accounts Receivable = 1,133,414.13

Sum of quick assets = 4,560,423.24 + 3,655,000.00 + 10,051.66 + 1,133,414.13  
Sum of quick assets = 9,358,889.03

Step 2: Total Current Liabilities = 1,124,588.25

Step 3: Calculate Quick Ratio = 9,358,889.03 / 1,124,588.25 â‰ˆ 8.32
